high.mackenzie.autumn.lang.compiler.typesystem.design

Interface IArrayType

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IExpressionType, IReferenceType, IReturnType, IType, IVariableType
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayType

    public interface IArrayType
extends IReferenceType, IVariableType
    An instance of this interface is the type of an array.

    • Method Detail

      • getElement

        IElementType getElement()
        This method returns the type of the elements that are in an array of this type.

        For example, this method will return type String, if this type is String[].

        Returns:
        the type of the elements in an array of this type.

      • getDimensions

        int getDimensions()
        This method returns the number of dimensions in an array of this type.

        For example, this method will return 1, if this type is String[]. Likewise, this method will return 3, if this type is String[][][].

        Returns:
        the dimensionality of an array of this type.

      • toClass

        java.lang.Class toClass()
        This method tries to return the java.lang.Class related to this type.
        Specified by:
        toClass in interface IReturnType
        Returns:
        the class-object representation of this type, if a class-object exists for this type; otherwise, return null.
